---
import BaseHead from "../components/BaseHead.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
import Header from "../components/Header.astro";
import { SITE_TITLE } from "../consts";
---

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead
			title={`About — ${SITE_TITLE}`}
			description="Learn about Veilus, the free anti-detect browser built on native Chromium for managing multiple accounts on one computer."
		/>
		<style>
			.about-content {
				max-width: 65ch;
			}
			.about-content h1 {
				margin-bottom: 1em;
			}
			.about-content h2 {
				margin-top: 2em;
				margin-bottom: 0.5em;
				color: var(--accent);
				font-size: 1.4em;
			}
			.about-content p {
				margin-bottom: 1.25em;
				color: var(--text-primary);
			}
			.about-content a {
				color: var(--accent);
			}
			.about-content table {
				width: 100%;
				border-collapse: collapse;
				margin: 1em 0;
				font-size: 0.95em;
			}
			.about-content th,
			.about-content td {
				padding: 0.6em 0.8em;
				border: 1px solid var(--border);
				text-align: left;
			}
			.about-content th {
				font-family: "Inter", sans-serif;
				font-weight: 600;
				background: var(--surface);
			}
			.community-links {
				display: flex;
				flex-wrap: wrap;
				gap: 1em;
				margin-top: 1em;
				list-style: none;
				padding: 0;
			}
			.community-links li a {
				display: inline-block;
				padding: 0.5em 1em;
				border: 1px solid var(--border);
				border-radius: 8px;
				text-decoration: none;
				font-family: "Inter", sans-serif;
				font-weight: 600;
				font-size: 0.9em;
				transition: border-color 0.15s ease, color 0.15s ease;
			}
			.community-links li a:hover {
				border-color: var(--accent);
			}
		</style>
	</head>
	<body>
		<Header />
		<main>
			<div class="about-content">
				<h1>About Veilus</h1>

				<h2>What is Veilus</h2>
				<p>
					Veilus is a free anti-detect browser for managing multiple
					accounts on one computer without getting detected or banned.
					Built on a native Chromium engine (not Electron), Veilus
					gives each browser profile a unique digital fingerprint —
					making every account look like it's running on a completely
					different device.
				</p>

				<h2>Who It's For</h2>
				<table>
					<thead>
						<tr>
							<th>User</th>
							<th>Use Case</th>
						</tr>
					</thead>
					<tbody>
						<tr>
							<td><strong>Affiliate Marketers</strong></td>
							<td>Run multiple ad accounts without linking</td>
						</tr>
						<tr>
							<td><strong>E-commerce Sellers</strong></td>
							<td>Manage storefronts on Amazon, Shopee, Lazada</td
							>
						</tr>
						<tr>
							<td><strong>Social Media Managers</strong></td>
							<td>Operate multiple social accounts safely</td>
						</tr>
						<tr>
							<td><strong>Web Scrapers</strong></td>
							<td>Collect data without IP/fingerprint bans</td>
						</tr>
						<tr>
							<td><strong>QA Engineers</strong></td>
							<td>Test under different device configurations</td>
						</tr>
					</tbody>
				</table>

				<h2>Key Features</h2>
				<p>
					<strong>Native Chromium engine</strong> — 3x faster page loads
					and 80% less RAM per profile compared to Electron-based alternatives.
					Real browser behavior with full Web API support.
				</p>
				<p>
					<strong>Fingerprint engine</strong> — each profile gets a mathematically
					consistent fingerprint covering Canvas, WebGL, AudioContext,
					fonts, screen, navigator, and WebRTC.
				</p>
				<p>
					<strong>VeilusFlow automation</strong> — record browser actions
					visually (clicks, typing, navigation) and replay them across
					profiles. No coding needed.
				</p>
				<p>
					<strong>Free to start</strong> — 5 profiles forever, no trial
					period, no credit card required.
				</p>

				<h2>How It Works</h2>
				<p>
					Each browser profile in Veilus gets three layers of
					isolation: a unique fingerprint (so websites see a different
					device), separate storage (cookies, cache, localStorage
					never leak between profiles), and an independent proxy
					connection (each profile gets its own IP). The result: every
					profile looks like a different computer on a different
					network.
				</p>

				<h2>Community</h2>
				<p>
					Join the conversation, get support, and stay updated.
					Contributors are welcome — check our
					<a
						href="https://github.com/nicholasgriffintn/veilus"
						target="_blank"
						rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub</a
					> to get involved.
				</p>
				<ul class="community-links">
					<li>
						<a
							href="https://t.me/veilusbrowser"
							target="_blank"
							rel="noopener noreferrer">Telegram</a
						>
					</li>
					<li>
						<a
							href="https://x.com/veilusbrowser"
							target="_blank"
							rel="noopener noreferrer">X (Twitter)</a
						>
					</li>
					<li>
						<a
							href="https://github.com/nicholasgriffintn/veilus"
							target="_blank"
							rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub</a
						>
					</li>
				</ul>

				<h2>This Blog</h2>
				<p>
					We write about multi-account management, browser
					fingerprinting, automation workflows, and product updates.
					Whether you're running ad accounts, managing storefronts, or
					looking for the right anti-detect setup — we've got guides
					for you.
				</p>
			</div>
		</main>
		<Footer />
	</body>
</html>
